@NatureFoodJnl The key point is that:
‚Äì The transport of food does not equal 20% of food emissions. It's more like 5-6%.

‚Äì Eating locally does not make a massive difference to food emissions, because transport tends to make up a small share.

@NatureFoodJnl The biggest problem with the initial paper is that it completely redefined 'food miles' to also include the transport of fertilizers, machinery, livestock etc.

These emissions are unrelated to the advice of 'eating locally'.

